Date: Mon, 27 Feb 2023 09:36:26 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 27/40] mm: prevent userfaults to be handled under per-vma lock

Due to the possibility of handle_userfault dropping mmap_lock, avoid fault
handling under VMA lock and retry holding mmap_lock. This can be handled
more gracefully in the future.

Signed-off-by: Suren Baghdasaryan <surenb@google.com>
Suggested-by: Peter Xu <peterx@redhat.com>
---
 mm/memory.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/memory.c b/mm/memory.c
index 555612d15..751aebc1b 100644
--- a/mm/memory.c
+++ b/mm/memory.c
@@ -5254,6 +5254,15 @@ struct vm_area_struct *lock_vma_under_rcu(struct mm_struct *mm,
 	if (!vma_start_read(vma))
 		goto inval;
 
+	/*
+	 * Due to the possibility of userfault handler dropping mmap_lock, avoid
+	 * it for now and fall back to page fault handling under mmap_lock.
+	 */
+	if (userfaultfd_armed(vma)) {
+		vma_end_read(vma);
+		goto inval;
+	}
+
 	/* Check since vm_start/vm_end might change before we lock the VMA */
 	if (unlikely(address < vma->vm_start || address >= vma->vm_end)) {
 		vma_end_read(vma);
